-- Lagarde Wants Stress Tests on Banks as Soon as Possible, Market News Says
-- David Whitehouse
-- 2010-06-17T06:52:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-17/lagarde-wants-stress-tests-on-banks-as-soon-as-possible-market-news-says.html

          
          
             French Finance Minister Christine
Lagarde is strongly in favor of stress tests on banks and wants
the results to be published as soon as possible, Market News
reported, citing Reuters.  
 Lagarde was cited as saying that French banks are willing
to undergo such tests, which she believes would show a clean
bill of health.  
 A spokesman for Lagarde was not immediately available for
comment.  
          
          


  


        